 Following the convention, we report phrase-level F1 score.
    The MUC7 dataset is a subset of the North American News Text Corpora annotated with a wide variety of entities including people, locations, organizations, temporal events, monetary units, and so on.
    Since there was no direct mapping from temporal events, monetary units, and other entities from MUC7 and the MISC label in the CoNLL03 dataset, we measure performance only on PER,ORG and LOC.
    Evaluation: There are several sources of inconsistency in annotation between MUC7 and CoNLL03.
    For example, since the MUC7 dataset does not contain the MISC label, in the sentence &#8220;balloon, called the Virgin Global Challenger&#8221; , the expression Virgin Global Challenger should be labeled as MISC according to CoNLL03 guidelines.
    However, the gold annotation in MUC7 is &#8220;balloon, called the [ORG Virgin] Global Challenger&#8221;.
